<h2>AI Search and Generative Engine Optimization</h2>
<p><a href="/blog/generative-engine-optimization-guide/">Generative engine optimization</a> is becoming a ranking factor. AI search engines like Google AI Overviews, ChatGPT, and Perplexity pull answers from websites that structure content clearly.</p>
<h3>WordPress for AI Search</h3>
<p>WordPress gives you full control over the signals that AI search engines use:</p>
<ul>
<li>Custom <a href="/blog/schema-markup-for-blog-posts/">schema markup</a> for every content type (FAQ, HowTo, Article, Product)</li>
<li><a href="/blog/llms-txt-guide/">llms.txt files</a> for AI crawler guidance</li>
<li>Granular control over <a href="/blog/ai-crawlers-guide/">AI crawler access</a> via robots.txt</li>
<li>Speakable schema for voice search optimization</li>
<li>Clean HTML output that AI parsers can process reliably</li>
</ul>
<p>You can optimize every page specifically for <a href="/blog/optimize-google-ai-overviews/">AI Overview inclusion</a>. WordPress gives you the markup flexibility that AI citation depends on.</p>
<h3>Wix for AI Search</h3>
<p>Wix automatically generates BlogPosting and LocalBusiness structured data. It handles basic schema well. But you cannot add custom schema types like HowTo, FAQ (beyond blog posts), or Speakable.</p>
<p>Wix recently added AI-related features in its SEO dashboard, including the ability to track how pages appear in ChatGPT responses. The built-in structured data is sufficient for simple content. Complex schema strategies require WordPress.</p>
<h3>Verdict: AI Search</h3>
<p><strong>WordPress wins.</strong> Full schema control and custom markup give WordPress sites more surface area for <a href="/blog/get-cited-ai-search/">AI search visibility</a>.</p>
<h2>Programmatic SEO at Scale</h2>
<p><a href="/blog/programmatic-seo-guide/">Programmatic SEO</a> generates hundreds or thousands of pages from structured data. Think city landing pages, product comparison pages, or directory listings.</p>
<p>WordPress handles programmatic SEO through custom post types, Advanced Custom Fields, and templating systems like Elementor or custom PHP templates. You can build 500 location pages from a CSV in an afternoon.</p>
<p>Wix does not support programmatic page generation. Every page requires manual creation. For businesses that need <a href="/blog/city-service-landing-pages-seo/">city-specific landing pages</a> or large-scale content generation, this is a hard limitation.</p>
<p><strong>WordPress wins.</strong> Programmatic SEO is not possible on Wix.</p>
